{
  "texts": [
    "In analogy to the quark sector, the matrix V ν L is set to the unit matrix and ( V ℓ L) † defines the PMNS matrix: ( V ℓ L) † = ÛPMNS.",
    "Hence, the remaining matrices in this sector are ÛPMNS and V e R. The parametrization of the rotation matrices can be found in [1].",
    "Appendix C contains the choice for the parameters of the CKM and PMNS matrices.",
    "After the fermion rotations, flavour violating Z ′ couplings are generated, as indicated below.• Couplings of left-handed down quarks to Z ′:∆ ij L = g Z ′ (2ϵ 1 + ϵ 2)V uj V * ui + (ϵ 1 + 2ϵ 2)V cj V * ci (i ̸ = j),(21)∆ ii L = g Z ′ 1 6 + (2ϵ 1 + ϵ 2)|V ui | 2 + (ϵ 1 + 2ϵ 2)|V ci | 2 -ϵ 1 -ϵ 2.",
    "(22)The generation index i = d, s, b is used to make the notation more transparent."
  ]
}